kernelcraft (0.1-1) kinetic; urgency=medium

  * New version 0.1:
    - provide --init command
    - ship default config in /etc/kernelcraft.conf

 -- Andrea Righi <andrea.righi@canonical.com>  Sat, 26 Nov 2022 14:39:58 +0100

kernelcraft (0.0.3-1) kinetic; urgency=medium

  * New version 0.0.3:
    - support multiple architectures (arm64, ppc64el, riscv64, s390x)
    - allow to use KernelCraft directly from any git repository (without
      creating a duplicate git repo in ~/.kernelcraft)
    - allow to remotely clean the git repo (using --clean with --build-host)

 -- Andrea Righi <andrea.righi@canonical.com>  Fri, 25 Nov 2022 15:25:08 +0100

kernelcraft (0.0.2-1) kinetic; urgency=medium

  * New version 0.0.2:
    - doc: add a referene to the KernelCraft ppa
    - doc: properly format command examples
    - doc: add a requirements section to README.md
    - deb: clarify tool description
    - doc: add another remote build example to README.md
    - cfg: drop xenial and trusty kernels from default config
    - run.py: update generic command description
    - run.py: properly initialize build environment for Ubuntu kernels
    - cfg: add Ubuntu lunar git repository
    - doc: update README.md
    - run.py: prevent deleting dump file when a target file is specified
    - run.py: append -kc to kernel version
    - run.py: introduce option --dump-file
    - run.py: add remote build host support
    - run.py: introduce option --dump
    - deb: update list of dependencies
    - run.py: get rid of the --local option
    - config: add arighi-rust git repository
    - run.py: introduce option --skip-build
    - run.py: make system directories rw using fs overlays
    - run.py: introduce option --clean
    - run.py: introduce --config FILE
    - documentation: update README.md
    - cfg: introduce a config file to define repositories
    - run.py: do not implicitly boot the kernel with nokaslr
    - run.py: minor command line arguments refactoring
    - run.py: rename option --resume to --local

 -- Andrea Righi <andrea.righi@canonical.com>  Wed, 09 Nov 2022 08:41:38 +0100

